> Warning: Final quality depends heavily on the input image and especially on the generated depth map. Artifacts or wrong depth separation in the map will directly degrade the effect. Different models (for example Apple Depth Pro vs Depth Anything) also produce different depth interpretations, which changes perceived effect intensity.

## Installation

<Steps>
	<Step title="Install the component">
		Run the following command to install the component and its dependencies:
		<InstallationTabs component="fake-3d-image" />
	</Step>
	<Step title="Import the component">
		Import the component into your Svelte file:

```ts
import { Fake3DImage } from "$lib/motion-core";
```

	</Step>
</Steps>

## Generate Depth Map

<Steps>
	<Step title="Choose a source image">
		Prepare a regular image that has clear depth separation.
	</Step>
	<Step title="Open DepthPro Grayscale">
		Go to
		<a
		    class="font-medium tracking-normal text-foreground underline decoration-dotted underline-offset-4 transition-[color] duration-150 ease-out hover:text-foreground-muted"
			href="https://huggingface.co/spaces/cubuvl/DepthPro-transformers-Grayscale"
			target="_blank"
			rel="noreferrer"
		>
			DepthPro Transformers Grayscale
		</a>.
	</Step>
	<Step title="Compute and download">
		Upload your image, generate the depth map, then download the grayscale result.
	</Step>
	<Step title="Use both files in component props">
		Set your image path in `colorSrc` and the generated depth map path in `depthSrc`.
	</Step>
</Steps>

